article.headline: Cornell 60, Princeton 51
article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. -- Ryan Wittman had 12 points to lead four players in double figures, senior center Jeff Foote had six points, nine rebounds and three blocks, and Cornell finished its season with a 60-51 victory over Princeton on Saturday night. Cornell (21-9, 11-3 Ivy), which captured the Ivy League title on Friday night to earn its second straight NCAA tournament berth, won for the 21st straight time at Newman Arena, the fourth-longest home streak in the nation. Louis Dale had 11 points, and freshman Chirs Wroblewski and Alex Tyler each had 10 for Cornell, which had four blocks to set a school record of 121. The previous record of 117 was set by the 1996-97 team. Douglas Davis led the Tigers (12-14, 7-6) with 16 points, and Patrick Saunders had 13 points and seven rebounds.
